The Nigeria Customs Service has deactivated Five Star Logistics from its portal as a result of unpaid assessment running into millions of naira.  In a a press release signed by the Ag National President, ANLCA, Farinto Kayode Collins, said “It has been brought to the notice of NECOM that our members are unable to exit the already Release VEHILCES and Cargoes from the five Star Logistics due to the fact that the terminal operator has been deactivated from Custons portal as a result of unpaid assessment running into millions of naira.”  Farinto stated that ANLCA is saddened with this situation and will definitely intervene appropriately. “We wish to inform our members that, ANLCA is on top of this issue and we are saddened about the development. However,we shall be given the terminal operator between now and next week Tuesday to resolve their issue with Nigeria Customs if not, ANLCA will be taking them to court for beach of agreement and failure to deliver these cargoes to the importers representative .  He added that Five Star Logistics will be responsible for every accrued charges during this face. “So also, five Star should know that, she will be responsible for all demurrages and storages that May accrue withing these period. ( from the 6th of July to date).  Farinto implored all ANLCA members to be law abiding in carrying out their businesses. “Finally we urge our members to be calm and be law abiding and I want to advice that we keep the receipts of all payments during these period. Do enjoy your weekend.”